markdown: <::Line graph showing % Change from Baseline over different visits. Y-axis: % Change from Baseline, with tick marks at -6, -4, -2, 0, 2, 4, 6. X-axis: Visit, with tick marks at Baseline, 12 Months, and 36 Months. A dashed horizontal line is present at 0% Change from Baseline. There are five data series represented by different markers and lines: - **Placebo** (black square marker): Starts at 0 at Baseline, decreases to approximately -1.8 at 12 Months, and further decreases to approximately -3.2 at 36 Months. - **CEE Only** (black diamond marker): Starts at 0 at Baseline, increases to approximately 3.8 at 12 Months, and further increases to approximately 4.8 at 36 Months. - **CEE/MPA (cyclic)** (black circle marker): Starts at 0 at Baseline, increases to approximately 3.0 at 12 Months, and further increases to approximately 4.0 at 36 Months. - **CEE/MPA (continuous)** (black upward triangle marker): Starts at 0 at Baseline, increases to approximately 3.0 at 12 Months, and further increases to approximately 4.2 at 36 Months. - **CEE/MP (cyclic)** (black downward triangle marker): Starts at 0 at Baseline, increases to approximately 3.5 at 12 Months, and further increases to approximately 5.0 at 36 Months. : chart::> Source: https://www.industrydocuments.ucsf.edu/docs/xkbw0217 DWRITE 071001
